8_SAS_On Cloud Models- Characteristics of Public Cloud.


Q1
What are the characteristics of Public cloud?
ANS
OWNERSHIP
MULTIPLE END USERS
PUBLIC ACCESS
AVAILABILITY
CONNECTIVITY
SKILLS
Q2
What is Ownership in the public cloud?
ANS
RESOURCES THE ORGANIZATION OR END USER USES : STORAGE, PROCESSING POWER, CPU, MEMORY, ETC.
Q3
What are Multiple End Users in the public cloud?
ANS
PUBLIC CLOUD PROVIDERS MAKE THEIR RESOURCES AVAILABLE TO MULTIPLE ORGANIZATIONS, NOT JUST ONE.
Q4
What is public access in the public cloud?
ANS
THE RESOURCES IN A PUBLIC CLOUD ARE ACCESSIBLE PUBLICLY THROUGH THE INTERNET
Q5
What is availability in the public cloud?
ANS
MOST COMMON CLOUD TYPE ENVIRONMENT MODEL : THE CLOUD PROVIDER ENSURES THE AVAILABILITY OF YOUR DATA AND MACHINES.
Q6
What is connectivity in the public cloud?
ANS
USERS AND ORGANIZATIONS ARE TYPICALLY CONNECTED TO THE PUBLIC CLOUD OVER THE INTERNET USING A WEB BROWSER.
Q7
What are skills in the public cloud?
ANS
THE PUBLIC CLOUDS DO NOT REQUIRE DEEP TECHNICAL KNOWLEDGE TO SET UP IN YOUR ORGANIZATION. YOU DONâ€™T NEED MANY RESOURCES AS WELL, YOU JUST NEED A DEVICE WITH A BROWSER AND INTERNET CONNECTION.
Q8
Public clouds do not require too much resources to run an organization? True/False.
ANS
TRUE
Q9
What are the basic things users might need to access public clouds?
ANS
DEVICE, INTERNET,
Q10
The skills in the public clouds are managed by the cloud providers? True/False.
ANS
TRUE


